      <prefercite id="aspace_48ad0da53e24978a30532dc523b65c89">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Emanuel Fritz Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4ff258c45522d62937f3189cde3082e7">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains papers of Emanuel Fritz (born 1886), a member of the Yale School of Forestry class of 1914, and later a professor of forestry at the University of California at Berkeley. The papers consist of class notes, notes on field work, examinations, and a report by Fritz dating from his study at Yale. Also included are Civil Service questions for foresters from 1913. The papers were donated to Yale University by Professor Fritz in 1976.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_5ebdaf69afb45c1d32b3ecacb72f4e28">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Emanuel Fritz: member of the Yale School of Forestry Class of 1914; later professor of forestry at the University of California at Berkeley.</p>
      </bioghist>
